---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Markdown from '../../components/Markdown.astro';

export async function getStaticPaths() {
    const posts = [
        {
            title: '1640 Labs Launch',
            slug: '1640-labs-launch',
            date: '2026-01-20',
            content: `
# 1640 Labs Launch

Today marks a significant milestone as we officially launch **1640 Labs**. Our mission is to bridge the gap between complex technological advancements and practical business strategy.

## What we do

We specialize in strategic consulting, helping organizations navigate the rapidly evolving landscape of:

- Distributed Systems
- Scalable Architecture
- Data Strategy
- Operational Efficiency

We believe that the best solutions are not just technically sound but are also aligned with the core business objectives.

## Looking Forward

This blog will serve as a hub for our research, insights, and case studies. Stay tuned for more deep dives into the technologies shaping our future.
            `
        },
        {
            title: 'Loonshot Ideas',
            slug: 'loonshot-ideas',
            date: '2026-01-15',
            content: `
# Loonshot Ideas

Most breakthrough innovations were initially dismissed as "crazy" or "unrealistic." These are what Safi Bahcall calls *Loonshots*.

## The Power of Fragility

The most important ideas are often the most fragile. They require protected environments—"nurseries"—where they can be nurtured without the pressure of immediate commercial success or the scrutiny of traditional metrics.

### Key Principles

1.  **Separate the Phases**: Keep your "artists" (working on loonshots) and "soldiers" (maintaining the core business) distinct.
2.  **Dynamic Equilibrium**: Ensure a constant flow of ideas and feedback between the two.
3.  **Manage the Transfer**: The transition from idea to product is where most loonshots fail.

In our consulting work, we help companies build the structures necessary to support these radical ideas while maintaining operational excellence.
            `
        },
        {
            title: 'Flux Capacity',
            slug: 'flux-capacity',
            date: '2026-01-10',
            content: `
# Flux Capacity: Scalability in Distributed Systems

In distributed computing, "capacity" isn't a static number. It's a dynamic variable that changes with network latency, data consistency requirements, and hardware reliability. We call this *Flux Capacity*.

## The Constraints

When building for scale, you must consider:

\`\`\`typescript
interface SystemConstraints {
  latency: number;
  consistency: 'strong' | 'eventual' | 'causal';
  throughput: number;
}
\`\`\`

Scaling isn't just about adding more servers; it's about managing the overhead of coordination.

### Lessons Learned

- **Backpressure is essential**: Systems must be able to signal when they are overwhelmed.
- **Observability over Monitoring**: Don't just watch for failures; understand the state of the entire system.
- **Automate Recovery**: The goal is resilience, not just uptime.

At 1640 Labs, we design systems that thrive in high-flux environments.
            `
        }
    ];

    return posts.map((post) => ({
        params: { slug: post.slug },
        props: { post },
    }));
}

const { post } = Astro.props;
---

<Layout title={`${post.title} | 1640 Labs`}>
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-12">
        <header class="mb-8">
            <a href="/blog" class="text-primary no-underline hover:underline mb-8 inline-block">&larr; Back to blog</a>
            <time class="text-sm text-gray-400 block mb-2">{new Date(post.date).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', day: 'numeric', year: 'numeric' })}</time>
            <h1 class="mb-0">{post.title}</h1>
        </header>
        <Markdown content={post.content} />
    </article>
</Layout>
